# Continue eBPF DFIR Installation

## Current Status

**Completed:**

- Visual Studio 2022 Community installed

- LLVM/Clang 18.1.8 installed and verified

- Repositories cloned (ebpf-for-windows and eBPF-for-DFIR)

- CMake installed

- NuGet installed and source configured (nuget.org)

**Last Action:** About to install WiX Toolset and retry NuGet restore

## Implementation Plan

### 1. Install WiX Toolset

- Install WiX Toolset v3.14.1 (required for building the MSI installer)

- Verify installation by checking for `candle.exe` in Program Files

### 2. Complete Repository Initialization

- Run `.\scripts\initialize_ebpf_repo.ps1` from the ebpf-for-windows directory

- This script will:

- Configure CMake

- Restore NuGet packages (should now succeed with WiX Toolset installed)

- Set up external dependencies

### 3. Build ebpf-for-windows

- Use Developer Command Prompt for VS 2022

- Build solution: `msbuild /m /p:Configuration=Debug /p:Platform=x64 ebpf-for-windows.sln`
- Verify build outputs in `x64\Debug` directory

### 4. Build eBPF-for-DFIR

- Build the eBPF-for-DFIR solution using MSBuild

- Verify all extension drivers build successfully:

- FileEventEbpfExt
- RegEventEbpfExt
- ProcEventEbpfExt
- NetEventEbpfExt

### 5. Enable Test Signing (if not already enabled)

- Check current test signing status

- Enable test signing if needed (requires Administrator and reboot)

- Note: This is required to load unsigned/test-signed drivers

### 6. Install eBPF Components

- Install ebpf-for-windows using the built MSI or setup script

- Install eBPF-for-DFIR extensions

- Verify services are running (EbpfSvc)

### 7. Verify Installation

- Test eBPF functionality with basic commands
- Verify DFIR extensions are loaded

- Test network forensics monitoring capabilities

## Key Files

- [ebpf-for-windows/scripts/initialize_ebpf_repo.ps1](ebpf-for-windows/scripts/initialize_ebpf_repo.ps1) - Repository initialization script

- [ebpf-for-windows/ebpf-for-windows.sln](ebpf-for-windows/ebpf-for-windows.sln) - Main solution file

- [eBPF-for-DFIR/eBPF-for-DFIR.sln](eBPF-for-DFIR/eBPF-for-DFIR.sln) - DFIR solution file

- [ebpf-for-windows/docs/GettingStarted.md](ebpf-for-windows/docs/GettingStarted.md) - Build documentation

- [eBPF-for-DFIR/docs/setup.md](eBPF-for-DFIR/docs/setup.md) - DFIR setup guide

## Notes

- WiX Toolset is required for building the MSI installer

- Test signing mode must be enabled to load unsigned drivers (development/testing only)

- All builds should use Developer Command Prompt for VS 2022 to ensure proper environment setup","numCharactersInRequestedRange":4182,"totalLinesInFile":142}
